CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 20, 1961, pg. 2 reads: "After The 'Ward Wars' Were Over...Fifth Ward Winners, Workers - The two-to-one tally scored by aldermanic candidate Robert E. (Pappy) Williams,...and incumbent constable candidate Thomas J. Smith, in Second District, Fifth Ward polling place...extended throughout the ward..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five men and three women standing in front of brick building, possibly McKelvy School, with window grilles and campaign posters for Aldermans H. Ryan, Sarah R. Kirk, and Erroll Davis and constable L. Washington and "Larry" Huff, during 1961 primary elections
